    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-14T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-14T22:00:00-05:00" n="89"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1133: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-15T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 15, 1930—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegram of May 14, noon. I have just received a radio message
                    from General Huang Shao-hung that American missionaries at Kweihsien prefer to
                    remain in their homes.</p>
                <pb facs="0215" n="117" xml:id="pg_117"/>
                <p>Cantonese authorities announce the capture of Sunchow, Kwangsi Province, after
                    heavy bombardment by airplanes and gunboats. All attacks on Kwangsi defenses at
                    various points appeared to have begun.</p>
                <p>Department and Legation informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
